# AuraMesh Backend Logic Implementation Plan

AuraMesh currently has its UI foundation and IndexedDB layer in place, but all runtime service calls are commented out. This plan wires in the full backend logic according to the README roadmap — covering app initialization, acoustic keyword detection, multi-modal alerts, and P2P mesh communication stubs.

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1 – App Initialization

#### [MODIFY] [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/adit1/Desktop/auramesh/src/App.tsx)
- Uncomment and activate [initializeApp()](file:///c:/Users/adit1/Desktop/auramesh/src/App.tsx#44-74) in the startup `useEffect`
- Uncomment the storage-polling `useEffect` (updates footer every 30s)
- Set `isInitialized` to `false` as default so the splash screen shows during load
- After init, boot all background services (acoustic, mesh)

---

### 2 – Acoustic Keyword Detection Service

#### [NEW] [acousticService.ts](file:///c:/Users/adit1/Desktop/auramesh/src/services/acousticService.ts)

A self-contained service built on **Web Audio API**. No external dependency needed for Phase 1 — uses energy-based voice activity detection (VAD) + keyword spotting via SpeechRecognition. Key design: all processing is **on-device only**.

- `startListening(onDetection, settings)` — requests mic, sets up `AudioContext` + `AnalyserNode`, attaches `webkitSpeechRecognition` (or `SpeechRecognition`) in continuous mode for keyword matching
- `stopListening()` — stops recognition and closes audio stream
- `getAudioLevel()` — returns current dB level (for UI indicator)
- On keyword match, calls `onDetection(keyword, confidence)` callback which triggers the store action [addKeywordDetection](file:///c:/Users/adit1/Desktop/auramesh/src/store/appStore.ts#129-147)
- Emergency keywords from user settings are matched (SOS, fire, help, earthquake, flood, danger, emergency)

> **No new npm package needed** — uses the browser's built-in Web Speech API (`SpeechRecognition`).

---

### 3 – Multi-Modal Alert Service

#### [NEW] [alertService.ts](file:///c:/Users/adit1/Desktop/auramesh/src/services/alertService.ts)

Dispatches alerts using all enabled modalities from user settings.

- `triggerAlert(event, settings)` — dispatches haptic + visual + audio based on `settings.alertModes`
- `hapticAlert(severity)` — calls `navigator.vibrate` with severity-coded patterns
  - critical: `[300, 100, 300, 100, 300]`
  - warning: `[200, 100, 200]`
  - info: `[100]`
- `visualAlert(severity)` — injects CSS class `alert-flash-[severity]` on `document.body`, auto-removes after animation
- `audioAlert(message)` — uses `SpeechSynthesisUtterance` to read the alert message aloud
- `playTone(freq, duration)` — plays a beep via `AudioContext` for environments where TTS is unavailable

> **No new npm package needed** — all browser native APIs.

---

### 4 – P2P Mesh Communication Service

#### [NEW] [meshService.ts](file:///c:/Users/adit1/Desktop/auramesh/src/services/meshService.ts)

Provides peer discovery and message relay. Uses **WebRTC** for same-network peers and **Web Bluetooth** for proximity peers. This is a Phase 3 stub that's architected for real data channels but uses simulation for discovery.

- `startMesh(onPeerUpdate, onMessageReceived)` — boot mesh scanning
- `stopMesh()` — teardown
- `broadcastSOS(message)` — relay SOS to all connected peers via RTCDataChannel
- `sendHeartbeat()` — periodic ping to keep peers alive
- `discoverPeers()` — scan BLE + WebRTC signaling (in Phase 3 this uses a signaling server; for now uses `BroadcastChannel` API within same browser for testing)
- Duplicate detection via UUID set
- Hop count enforcement (max 5 hops)
- Peer data is stored via `dbService.savePeer` and surfaced in store via [updatePeer](file:///c:/Users/adit1/Desktop/auramesh/src/store/appStore.ts#162-185)

> **No new npm package needed** — uses browser-native WebRTC, Web Bluetooth, and BroadcastChannel APIs.

